The paper focuses on evolutionary robotics, which is a subfield of robotics that uses evolutionary algorithms to design and optimize robots. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of behavioural diversity and novelty search, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the interaction between agents and their environment, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses evolutionary algorithms to optimize the behaviour of the agents, which is a common technique in the field of neural networks and evolutionary computation (cs.NE).
